```xml
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.smartprime-874774.android-automation-tool">

    <!-- Application configuration -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">
        
        <!-- Main activity for the application -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN"/>
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER"/>
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- Service for handling automation operations -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:exported="false">
            <!-- AutomationService manages background tasks for social media automation -->
        </service>

    </application>

    <!-- Permissions required for functionality -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <!-- Allows access to the internet for automated operations on platforms such as Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok -->
  
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
    <!-- Allows checking network connectivity status before attempting automated operations -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- Required to read media files that might be shared or posted during automation -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- Required to save media files or logs generated by the automation process -->

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Components:
- **Application**: The main application element contains overall application settings such as the icon, label, and theme.
- **MainActivity**: This is the primary activity that launches the application, serving as the user interface where users can configure automation settings.
- **AutomationService**: A background service dedicated to managing the automation tasks. This service can run continuously to perform scheduled tasks and handle operations without requiring user interaction.

### Permission Declarations:
- **INTERNET**: This permission is essential for the application to communicate with social media platforms for automated actions.
- **ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE**: It allows the app to monitor network status so it can effectively manage automated operations based on connectivity.
- **READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE**: Grants access to read files from the external storage, which may be necessary for posting content.
- **WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE**: Required to write data to external storage, such as saving logs or media files used during automation processes.

This configuration is designed to support the MadHub product's features and functionality while ensuring compliance with Android development standards.
